.Dd May 25, 2026
.Dt XTC_VERSION_COMPONENTS 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_version_components
.Nd decompose the xtc library version into integer components
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_version_components "int *major" "int *minor" "int *patch"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn xtc_version_components
function writes the SemVer
.Em major ,
.Em minor ,
and
.Em patch
components of the library version into the integers pointed to by
.Fa major ,
.Fa minor ,
and
.Fa patch
respectively.
.Pp
Every output component is a non-negative integer.
The components agree with the leading numeric portion of the string
returned by
.Xr xtc_version_string 3 .
.Sh RETURN VALUES
On success the function returns
.Dv XTC_OK
.Pq 0 .
.Pp
If any of
.Fa major ,
.Fa minor ,
or
.Fa patch
is
.Dv NULL ,
the function returns
.Dv XTC_E_INVAL
without modifying any output parameter.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
#include <stdio.h>
#include <xtc.h>

int main(void) {
        int maj, min, pat;
        if (xtc_version_components(&maj, &min, &pat) == XTC_OK)
                printf("xtc %d.%d.%d\en", maj, min, pat);
        return 0;
}
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc 7 ,
.Xr xtc_version_string 3 ,
.Xr xtc_strerror 3
.Sh HISTORY
First appeared in xtc 0.0.1.
